<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7488> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7488" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He is known only with the title # in an inscription of Messenia (IG 5.1.1432). If he was a governor of the Macedonian province, he should be placed between C. Memmius and T. Didius, therefore probably in 102 (Sumner, Orators 89; MRR 1.564, 103 B.C.). See above, on C. Memmius (5 and 3).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3585> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3585" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Termed {Gr} though he might also be a Propraetor (IG 5.1.1432, in Messenia)." .
